            <p class="core">The only variation permeating these places seems to be the rain, alternating with the mist. Yet, despite this apparent lack of natural warmth, there's a sense of belonging here. You feel at ease, warmed by human connection, by the simple joy of living, and by the shared experience of just being. No matter where we come from, it feels like home.
            <br><br>
